In a bowl, stir together chevre and lemon juice. Mix in shallots, parsley, rosemary, thyme, and salt and pepper to taste. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and chill up to 3 days. Four hours ahead, prepare vegetables. At least 2 hours ahead, remove spread from refrigerator. Spoon spread into a serving bowl and garnish with fresh chives, snipped and whole. Arrange vegetables and crackers on a platter. Nest bowl of cheese spread in center and serve.